FBIS4-62626 "drsov096_a_94014" FBIS-SOV-94-096 Daily Report 17 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Grachev Proposes Withdrawal Ceremony in Reichstag Grachev Proposes Withdrawal Ceremony in Reichstag PM1705124394 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 17 May 94 p 3 PM1705124394 Moscow IZVESTIYA Russian BFN [Boris Lysenko report: "Pavel Grachev Proposes Holding Reichstag Session"] [Text] Berlin -- Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev has voiced a desire to include a session in the Reichstag building as part of the ceremonies to mark the Russian troops withdrawal from Germany. We can assume that the discussion of this proposal from Pavel Grachev will not be easy. Such a request was made last year by Colonel General Matvey Burlakov, commander in chief of the Western Group of Forces, but nobody took it seriously at the time.
